TinyGL now exposes an OpenGL ES 1.1 Common-Lite shaped API.
Functions not declared by include/GLES/gl.h are outside the supported
public surface.

Implemented core paths:

- Fixed-point transforms, lighting, materials, clear state, texture state,
  and matrix stacks.
- glDrawArrays and glDrawElements for points, lines, line strips, line loops,
  triangles, triangle strips, and triangle fans.
- Vertex arrays for GL_BYTE, GL_SHORT, and GL_FIXED vertex, normal, and
  texcoord data. Color arrays support GL_FIXED and GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE.
  GL_FLOAT is intentionally rejected with GL_INVALID_ENUM.
- Array and element buffer objects for GL_ARRAY_BUFFER and
  GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER.
- 2D texture uploads for alpha, luminance, luminance-alpha, RGB, and RGBA
  unsigned-byte data, plus RGB565/RGBA4444/RGBA5551 packed unsigned-short
  data. Uploaded textures are still resized to the renderer's 256x256
  backing format.
- glTexSubImage2D on the current 256x256 backing image.
- glGetError with first-error retention for validation failures.

Known limitations:

- EGL is not implemented.
- Floating-point GL entry points are not part of this Common-Lite build.
- Desktop OpenGL immediate mode, display lists, selection/name stack,
  polygon mode, quads, polygons, feedback, accumulation, evaluators,
  raster-position APIs, and color-index APIs are not public API.
- Mipmapping parameters are accepted, but the renderer uses level 0 only.
- Compressed texture and extension texture upload paths are unsupported and
  report GL errors.
- Depth testing remains tied to the existing TinyGL rasterizer behavior:
  triangle fills use the zbuffer path, and explicit depth-test toggling is
  mainly meaningful for lines.
- Verification is currently Nspire-build coverage plus manual device testing.
- Only the core APIs are supported; no extensions.
